Flags are an element of syntax in Stu script that look like options in the shell.  They
apply to dependencies. They can be thought as applying to each edge in the dependency
graph.

The currently existing flags are listed in the manpage.

Possible future flags:
-d         Change directory
-i         Interactive (following commands needs to be executed in the foreground)
-a/-s      Additional dependencies
<...and others...>
